---
description: LGTM episode.json — orchestration touchpoint, approval gate, paths. Complements creative-director and renderer agents.
globs: episodes/**/episode.json
alwaysApply: false
---

When editing `episode.json` for LGTM:

- **Canonical orchestration:** `.claude/agents/creative-director.md` and project rule `lgtm-pipeline-orchestration.mdc` (always-on pipeline).
- **Human gate:** Do not set `approved: true` unless the human has reviewed the storyboard package; agents must not flip approval on their own.
- **Paths:** All paths in `episode.json` (and `storyboard.json`) are relative to the episode directory root (`tts/`, `clips/`, `output/`, etc.).
- **Render:** Only run `render/renderer.py` after `approved` is `true`, storyboard exists, and every non-empty VO has a real `audio_file`. See `lgtm-agent-renderer.mdc` and `.claude/agents/renderer.md`.
- **Clip sources:** `clip_sources` order controls clip-sourcer; API keys live in `.env`. See `lgtm-agent-clip-sourcer.mdc`.
